setApplicationReferences

void setApplicationReferences(LewisSketch applicationRef,
                              LsUtils utilitiesRef,
                              Stack<Molecule> theUndoStackRef,
                              Stack<Molecule> theRedoStackRef)
Method to be invoked in main application's init(). Methods of this class need to access methods and objects in the main application object. setOtherElementField added separately.

Parameters:
applicationRef - reference to the LewisSketch application
utilitiesRef - a LsUtils object
theUndoStackRef - the undo stack
theRedoStackRef - the redo stack

setGUIButtons

void setGUIButtons(JToggleButton periodicChart,
                   JToggleButton undo,
                   JToggleButton redo)
Sets the GUI buttons. At times the action listener needs to change attributes of some buttons on the GUI, so references to these buttons should be given when the application is initialized.

Parameters:
periodicChart - button to choose an element
undo - the undo button
redo - the redo button

setStartData

void setStartData(Molecule givenData)
Sets the start data. It is made "current" when undo stack is empty.
